// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa — P1 (proposal stack paradigm bootstrap)
//
//  PURPOSE
//    First tool in the docs/anima_proposal_stack_paradigm_20260422.md series.
//    Bootstraps the **proposal stack** state directory (state/proposals/) so
//    every later tool (P2 emit, P3 review, P4 approve/reject/implement,
//    P5 dashboard, P6 lineage, P7 cluster, P8 conflict, P9 12h loop) can
//    rely on a stable on-disk schema.
//
//    Per the spec the goal is a **rejection of automatic module creation**:
//    new ideas are NOT spawned as code — they are emitted as proposals into
//    state/proposals/pending/ and only transition to modules under explicit
//    user approval. This tool creates exactly that holding-tank infra.
//
//  DIRECTORY LAYOUT (spec §1)
//    state/proposals/
//      ├── inventory.json                  (single SSOT meta index)
//      ├── pending/                        (awaiting user review)
//      ├── refinement/                     (per-id versioned refine history)
//      ├── approved/                       (user approved, awaiting impl)
//      ├── rejected/                       (user rejected + reason)
//      ├── archived/                       (impl complete, permanent record)
//      ├── debate/                         (conflicting proposals)
//      ├── clusters/                       (5+ related → cluster candidates)
//      └── meta/
//          ├── metrics.json                (counters, refreshed each cycle)
//          ├── lineage.json                (parent/child proposal graph)
//          └── decay_log.json              (stale-pending decay events)
//
//  SCHEMAS
//    inventory.json
//      { "schema": "anima/proposal_inventory/1",
//        "ts": "<iso>",
//        "tool": "tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa",
//        "proposals": [],
//        "summary": { "pending": 0, "refinement": 0, "approved": 0,
//                     "rejected": 0, "archived": 0, "debate": 0,
//                     "clusters": 0, "total": 0 } }
//
//    meta/metrics.json
//      { "schema": "anima/proposal_metrics/1",
//        "ts": "<iso>",
//        "total_pending": 0, "total_refinement": 0, "total_approved": 0,
//        "total_archived": 0, "total_rejected": 0, "total_debate": 0,
//        "total_clusters": 0,
//        "approval_rate_30d": 0.0, "implementation_lag_days": 0.0,
//        "median_age_pending_days": 0.0, "evolution_velocity": 0.0,
//        "user_review_lag_days": 0.0,
//        "top_clusters": [], "highest_score_pending": [] }
//
//    meta/lineage.json
//      { "schema": "anima/proposal_lineage/1",
//        "ts": "<iso>",
//        "nodes": [], "edges": [] }
//
//    meta/decay_log.json
//      { "schema": "anima/proposal_decay_log/1",
//        "ts": "<iso>",
//        "events": [] }
//
//  PROPOSAL CARD (spec §2 v1) — emitted at pending/20260422-001_sample.json
//    The first proposal is **this very task** (P1 inventory bootstrap),
//    so the proposal stack starts non-empty and proves the schema by
//    example. The card mirrors §2 verbatim with concrete values.
//
//  USAGE
//    hexa run tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa            (idempotent init)
//    hexa run tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa --selftest (verify 8 dirs +
//                                                           3 meta json valid)
//    hexa run tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa --status   (print counts)
//    hexa run tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa --reset    (DRY by default)
//    hexa run tool/proposal_inventory_init.hexa --reset --apply
//                                                          (DESTRUCTIVE —
//                                                           wipes + rewrites)
//
//  IDEMPOTENCY
//    Re-running with no flags only creates anything that is missing. Existing
//    files are never overwritten (so manual edits to inventory.json or any
//    proposal card are preserved). The sample proposal is only emitted on
//    fresh init when pending/ is empty.
//
//  HARD CONSTRAINTS (spec §13 anti-patterns)
//    - DO NOT touch .roadmap (uchg + user gate)
//    - DO NOT modify tool/, config/, docs/ — only state/proposals/ writes
//    - DO NOT auto-implement anything (this tool only seeds storage)
//    - DO NOT spawn duplicate proposals on rerun
//    - reject 영원한 destruction without explicit --apply
//
//  RAW
//    raw#9 hexa-only · raw#10 deterministic · raw#11 snake_case
//    raw#12 실측 only · raw#15 no-hardcode (paths anchored to constants)
//
//  EXIT CODES
//    0 — init OK / selftest pass / status printed / reset dry preview
//    1 — selftest fail
//    2 — io / setup error
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

